profile_positions.description:
International Business Controller

Activities:	Overview and control of international productions and investments throughout Europe (The Netherland, Germany, United Kingdom, Spain, Italy and France), Russia (Moscow) and USA (Las Vegas) which involves:
	Business Case preparation and review for future productions and investments;
	Budget control and reporting overview for the theatre (FOH) and musical business;
	Review and application of investment structures for licensing arrangements and royalties proposals;
	Management of production investments;
	Developing, implementing and reviewing business reporting formats, procedures and structures for international productions and sales activities;
	Liaise with Finance Directors and Production Controllers with regard to production licensing obligations ( to Disney Theatrical, Little Star, ZLL), production performance, production reporting, sales reporting and overview;
	Reporting to the International Executive Producer and Board of Directors for all international productions and concerning new production business case proposals.

Activities:	Overview and control of international productions and investments throughout Europe ( The Netherlands, Germany, France, Spain ) and USA ( Las Vegas ) with the International Business Manager which involves:
	Part of the international Business and Production Unit which was responsible for providing “know how” on production start up and controlling during the expanding of Stage Holding Germany who went from 1 to 7 Theatres and having 6 opening nights within one year ( Hamburg, Stuttgart, Berlin, Essen );
	Standardising production ( focussed on cost controlling), front of house ( food and beverage and merchandise) and sales reporting for all international productions and theatres;
	Financial Controller of the new business Hans Klok within Stage Holding BV in The Netherlands and Las Vegas;
	Designing and implementing a Production Reporting program especially created for Stage Holding;
	Reporting to the International Business Manager and Board of Directors for all international productions and concerning new production business case proposals.
